RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 1 5F All Weather Track CR: 70. Maiden Special Weight Purse 30000. (PLUS UP TO 30% PABF) FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. (Limited To10 Starters).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: YEAH TAKE THAT set the pressured pace off of the inside, shook clear leaving the turn, was headed a furlong out, fought back doggedly to prevail. A BIT OF CAPTAIN prompted the pace outside, angled in entering the stretch snugging up FRIZZANTE near the seven-sixteenths pole, switched back to the outside on the turn, poked his head in front a furlong out, battled on but was unable to best the determined winner. GRUMPY BROOKSIE settled in hand, looped up four wide through the turn, loomed a danger entering the stretch, but flattened in the final furlong. FRIZZANTE was forwardly placed along the inside, was caught in tight when A BIT OF CAPTAIN came in near the seven-sixteenths pole, checked losing position, churned on but failed to threaten thereafter. ZHU DADDY brushed the gate and came away behind his field, pulled to contention between horses, but came up empty leaving the turn and dropped out.

ENTRY.COMMENT: forwardly placed inside, in tight, checked 7/16, churned on

RACE.RACE_TEXT: RACE 2 1M 70Y All Weather Track CR: 80. Claiming Purse 14000. (PLUS UP TO 30% PABF) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES OR WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. RACE.FOOTNOTES: REDHOT KATIE settled saving ground while never far back, shifted out to commence her rally on the second turn, split rivals leaving the quarter pole, wore down TUDOX RUE MAJESTIC inside the furlong marker and edged clear. TUDOX RUE MAJESTIC opened clear to set the pace, was collared nearing the furlong marker, was unable to resist the winner but fought on to preserve the place spot. SCOOP THERE IT IS hopped at the start to get away slow, was rank to place through the first turn, leveled into stride on the backstretch, worked her way forward through the second turn off of the inside, angled to the rail a furlong out, got through and was making up ground. CAGUA contended between runners, circled four wide into the stretch to make her bid, but failed to sustain the drive. SUMTING RIGHT tracked three deep, moved up to engage the leader nearing the quarter pole, but came up empty between horses in the drive and faded. JEFF'S ANGEL broke slow and was squeezed, was unhurried off of the inside but failed to respond when asked. ROLLING MO was forwardly placed along the inside to the stretch and stopped.
